				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="October Hammer: A Mini Miniatures Game for the Russian Civil War" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Reds, Whites, anarchists, nationalists, Freikorps, Polish army.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Russian Civil War is a fascinating period to war game and with October Hammer you can do so easily, quickly and without a huge investment.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;October Hammer is what we call a &amp;quot;Mini Miniatures Game&amp;quot;: A game that is playable with simple rules, a small collection of figures and for a low price of entry.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Using the same game engine as Squad Hammer and Trench Hammer, the rules are aimed at Beer &amp;amp; Pretzels gaming but with plenty of chrome.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The core mechanics are simple and can be taught in minutes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Games are intended to be short, allowing you to get a rematch the same evening, even with multiple participants.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rules cover:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Various troop types from machine guns to partisans to armored cars.&amp;#10;     Optional and advanced rules to customize your game.&amp;#10;     Campaign and scenario set up rules.&amp;#10;     Army lists for 15 different forces, allowing you to quickly generate a force through a combination of random roll and selection systems.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Playable with both individual figures and with figures organized on troop stands.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can begin a new war gaming period without owning more than a few stands worth of troops.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules are laid out to be as screen and print friendly as possible.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;80's nostalgia look.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
